{{also|twenty-four/seven}}
==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|24/7}}, {{l|en|24-7}}, {{l|en|twenty-four/seven}}

===Etymology===
Shortened from "twenty-four hours a day, seven days a week".

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# 24 hours per day, seven days per week. Designates a [[round the clock|round-the-clock]] service, typically including holidays, as might be offered by a [[supermarket]], [[ATM]], [[gas station]], [[concierge]] service or manned data center.
#: ''They're open '''twenty-four seven'''; you can go there any time you want.''
# {{lb|en|colloquial}} Constantly, without interruption.
#* {{quote-song|en|year=2000|title=[[w:Stan (song)|Stan]]|composer=[[w:Eminem|Eminem]]|album=[[w:The Marshall Mathers LP|The Marshall Mathers LP]]|passage=My girlfriend's jealous 'cause I talk about you '''twenty-four seven'''}}

